{"TopicId":132775,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.8.1] Hangar Grid: Zero deviation [v0.4.0.181] (2019 Nov, 18)","CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T15:07:24Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-25T18:32:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EOfficially verified KSP 1.3.0 compatibility\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-25T14:05:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncan also confirm it\u0027s working fine in v1.3.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wcmille","CreatedById":151345,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-28T19:48:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would it take to make this available on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rayden","CreatedById":171352,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-26T18:26:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223280019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517168892\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wcmille\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/28/2018 at 1:48 PM, Wcmille said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would it take to make this available on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpen \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 Go to Settings -\u0026gt; Compatible KSP Versions.\u00A0 Make sure version 1.3.0.1804 is checked.\u00A0 If not checked then check it.\u00A0 Hit Save.\u00A0 Now it should appear on the list.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theonegalen","CreatedById":71012,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T03:58:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout to try this in 1.4.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Seems to be working just fine!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T04:31:43Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 04:31  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by theonegalen\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-12T10:31:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520567934\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271012\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022theonegalen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 09.03.2018 at 6:58 AM, theonegalen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout to try this in 1.4.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Seems to be working just fine!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! How did it happen that I\u0027m unaware of 1.4 is out...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Virtualgenius","CreatedById":67644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-13T06:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love this mod can align stuff spot on a must have as far as I am concerned\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Virtualgenius","CreatedById":67644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T09:10:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Ser will this be updated to 1.4.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T17:42:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223392460\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528103418\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267644\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Virtualgenius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Virtualgenius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Ser will this be updated to 1.4.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it still works, doesn\u0027t it? Though metadata isn\u0027t updated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T18:21:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill works great for me in 1.4.3. I wish it *wouldn\u0027t* work when typing in the aircraft notes box, but that\u0027s just a visual light show/annoyance. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Virtualgenius","CreatedById":67644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-04T19:58:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Ser yes it still works I just try to run mods for the release I am running thats all\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-05T15:15:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EOfficially verified KSP 1.4.x compatibility\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lilbat","CreatedById":137102,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-10T17:47:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to stick a line on a line of the grid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"frencrs","CreatedById":95489,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-11T03:45:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223413443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531244868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137102\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lilbat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, lilbat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to stick a line on a line of the grid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you mean have the selected part\u0027s axis lines snap to grid lines? Ex: While in the editor\u0027s translation mode you would be able to press a key over a grid line and have the part snap to that line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lilbat","CreatedById":137102,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-12T10:09:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223413714\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531280756\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295489\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022frencrs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/11/2018 at 5:45 AM, frencrs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you mean have the selected part\u0027s axis lines snap to grid lines? Ex: While in the editor\u0027s translation mode you would be able to press a key over a grid line and have the part snap to that line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but not only making them parralel but also placing them at the same place\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-17T12:07:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223414279\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531390181\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137102\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lilbat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/12/2018 at 1:09 PM, lilbat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but not only making them parralel but also placing them at the same place\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently you can match them only manually. What do you mean by \u0022the same place\u0022 for lines? Do you need to restrict a part\u0027s movement to a certain axis?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-17T12:10:17Z\u0022 title=\u002207/17/2018 12:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 17, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Ser\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Apaseall","CreatedById":176515,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-17T18:52:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMirror and fine adjust can help with getting things to line up. As we know this mod rotates, but does not translate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aeroboi","CreatedById":186653,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-08T09:52:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/104207-ser/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022104207\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/104207-ser/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Ser\u003C/a\u003E This mod makes alignment a tad bit easier then in stock imo using the keys. Stock has the absolute mode which does the same job also.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy question is why I would want this over the stock absolute rotation mode since that does the same job for me?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs it just to make it that little bit easier or is there more to it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-08T09:52:39Z\u0022 title=\u002209/08/2018 09:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Aeroboi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-11T08:46:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223447331\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221536400335\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186653\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aeroboi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/8/2018 at 12:52 PM, Aeroboi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/104207-ser/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022104207\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/104207-ser/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Ser\u003C/a\u003E This mod makes alignment a tad bit easier then in stock imo using the keys. Stock has the absolute mode which does the same job also.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy question is why I would want this over the stock absolute rotation mode since that does the same job for me?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs it just to make it that little bit easier or is there more to it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe absolute mode enables you to make something face straight forward or up while still doing it manually (with the help of angle snap). With this mod you can exactly align everything, e.g. control surfaces to angled wings by just pressing the key. Watch the video linked at \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T12:07:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this fantastic mod works on 1.5 ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vicdoctor","CreatedById":169932,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T12:14:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works fantastic!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T13:25:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just don\u0027t understand how you can \u0022not use\u0022 this mod! \u00A0The only mod to be sure everything is perfectly aligned!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-08T13:27:26Z\u0022 title=\u002211/08/2018 01:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by gilflo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-09T07:58:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003EVerified to work with KSP 1.5.1\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DfA-DoM","CreatedById":160709,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-26T10:39:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the record, this tremendously useful add-on \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003Eis still working in v1.6.1\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/104207-ser/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022104207\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/104207-ser/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Ser\u003C/a\u003E, I \u0027d love to have this taken in account in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(and BTW, same applies to \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155178-122-analog-control-continued\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EAnalog Control Continued\u003C/a\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-26T10:43:37Z\u0022 title=\u002203/26/2019 10:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by DfA-DoM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DfA-DoM","CreatedById":160709,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-12T06:57:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223569043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553596753\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160709\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DfA-DoM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/26/2019 at 11:39 AM, DfA-DoM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the record, this tremendously useful add-on \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003Eis still working in v1.6.1\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...and \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003Ealso in v1.7.0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease, update the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E accordingly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}